,Recommended,451990,31150859,Posted: 15 April,all,nymphe,"I was looking for some small and short games which I like to play occasionally and stumbled upon to this little gem couple of weeks ago. After my purchase I realized how wrong I was thinking.Gameplay:The game looks simple at the beginning. Indeed, there is almost no learning curve, but after your first race it hits you hard that the game is not like your average racing game. It is difficult to win a race and it is also not easy to get used to the viewing angle. Although there are some comments about how bad the viewing angle is, I personally liked it. The cars with different speeds and different handling ratios are well balanced and shows how difficult those cars were handled in 20’s. It is definitely not a simulation, and I don’t think this was the developer’s intention, but they managed to program the physics of the game remarkably good.Long story short: It takes a while to master but the game is very enjoyable.Graphics and Sound:The polygon graphics are funny and gives a great atmosphere to the game. It is a mixture of a comic book and art concept.There are some graphical glitches occasionally but nothing which will distract or annoy.The music is beautiful and doesn’t disturb if you play long. I’m not a fan of this era in terms of music, but when you hear it, you will be in the mood.I’ve played this game on my 15” Macbook Pro from 2011 on both macOS and Windows 10, and the performance was very good.Overall surprising great game which I recommend to everyone. A little bit patience for mastering the game is recommended. :)"
